"n.圣像，偶像 【英】 n. 圣像，偶像(an image or picture of Jesus, Mary, a saint, etc) 【记】 icon本身可作构词成 分，如iconize(肓目 崇拜)，iconoclasm( 打破圣像的行动) 无 【记】形意近idol；音：爱孔，敬爱孔子这个圣人，近年世界流行孔子热，“己所不欲，勿施于人”，“民为贵，君为轻”等孔子的仁义思想广为流传 icon (n.)  also ikon, 1570s, ""image, figure, representation,"" from Late Latin icon, from Greek eikon ""likeness, image, portrait,"" related to eikenai ""be like, look like,"" of unknown origin. Eastern Church sense is attested from 1833. Computing sense first recorded 1982."
